  "body": "On macs that use the GNU tooling over BSD, the build fails with the following error. The date error below seems to be a symptom of the sed issue.\r\n\r\n```\r\n% ./build/run make -j4                                                                                     17-11-17 - 11:18:40\r\n==== building the cross container (this could take minutes the first time)\r\n=== cross build image failed for build-f18d7920/cross-amd64\r\ndate: invalid option -- 'v'\r\nTry 'date --help' for more information.\r\ndate: invalid option -- 'v'\r\nTry 'date --help' for more information.\r\n=== docker build build-f18d7920/rootfs-builder-amd64\r\nsed: can't read s|BASEIMAGE|ubuntu:zesty|g: No such file or directory\r\nmake[1]: *** [Makefile:36: rootfs-build] Error 2\r\nmake: *** [Makefile:27: base.linux_amd64] Error 2\r\n```",
